HEADWORD: Ecbolic
<hw>Ec*bol"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Ecbole</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A drug, as ergot, which
by exciting uterine contractions promotes the expulsion of the contents
of the uterus.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

